<!--
  Android vector drawable for the search/leading-icon glyph rendered inside
  the Compose `OutlinedTextField.LeadingIcon` slot in
  `src/components/SearchOverlay.tsx`.

  This asset is the Android-safe icon source for the Compose icon slot
  required by the `runtime-android-icons-visible` regression fix:

  - The path uses `fillColor` (not stroke) so the `@expo/ui/jetpack-compose`
    `Icon` component's `VectorIconLoader.parsePathElement` can apply the
    `tint` prop (`colors.onSurfaceVariant`) to recolor the glyph at
    runtime for light and dark themes.
  - The `viewportWidth` / `viewportHeight` match the lucide 24x24 design
    grid so the rendered glyph is the same visual size as the lucide
    `Search` icon used in the home search launcher
    (`src/components/HomeSearchLauncher.tsx`).
  - The path is the standard Material Design magnifying-glass outline
    (closed filled shape that traces the outer edge of the lens and
    handle). The visual result is a single recognizable search glyph in
    both light and dark themes regardless of the Android system font
    catalog.
-->
